message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Agent Security Sandbox: A Benchmark for Evaluating Defenses Against Indirect Prompt Injection in LLM Agents"
version: 0.2.0
date-released: 2025-01-01
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/zhaoyifan/agent-security-sandbox"
repository-code: "https://github.com/zhaoyifan/agent-security-sandbox"
keywords:
  - prompt-injection
  - ai-safety
  - llm-agents
  - agent-security
  - benchmark
authors:
  - family-names: Zhao
    given-names: Yifan
abstract: >-
  A modular research framework for systematically evaluating
  the security of LLM-based agents against Indirect Prompt
  Injection (IPI) attacks. Provides a benchmark suite of 235
  test cases across 7 attack types, 5 pluggable defense
  strategies, and automated evaluation with both rule-based
  and LLM-based judges. Supports OpenAI, Anthropic, and
  OpenAI-compatible API providers with function calling and
  text ReAct modes.
